{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "BlossomWire",
  "description": "Scene 3 probe - the scanned apricot blossom cluster as a true line wireframe. A hard-decimated cut of the scan (blossom_wire.glb, 3070 tris / 9210 flat verts, Blender quadric collapse from the 80k LOD) feeds the Wireframe-preset pipeline with meshes instead of polytopes: gltf_mesh_source -> rotate_3d (slow time spin) -> flatten_3d perspective -> draw_lines points, while node.mesh_edges (NEW atom, this branch: per-triangle edge topology from the flat triangle list, index arithmetic only) supplies draw_lines edges. gltf max_capacity is sized EXACTLY to the asset (9210) - mesh_edges derives edge count from buffer capacity, so a zero-filled tail would draw dot edges at vertex 0 (documented v1 limitation).",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "BlossomWire",
    "displayName": "Blossom Wire",
    "category": "Geometry",
    "oscPrefix": "blossomwire",
    "available": true,
